&lt;li&gt;Develop and maintain a comprehensive video archive that allows for fast repurposing of content for editorial, social, and sponsored use&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Publish all assigned content across Forbes YouTube channels, Forbes.com and additional third-party distribution platforms. Responsibilities include writing performance-optimized titles, descriptions, tags and creating thumbnails and playlists&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Regularly monitor analytics across platforms to provide actionable insights on audience retention and growth&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support the podcast team by posting audio files to relevant distribution channels&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist production for Forbes summits and conferences. Lead post-production workflows to turn live event footage, backstage interviews and social content into polished digital assets&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with the social strategy team to deliver assets for social-first projects&lt;/li&gt;
