&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Forbes is an iconic global media brand that has symbolized success for over a century. Fueled by journalism that informs and inspires, Forbes spotlights the doers and doings shaping industries, achieving success and making an impact on the world. Forbes connects and convenes the most influential communities ranging from billionaires, business leaders and rising entrepreneurs to creators and innovators. The Forbes brand reaches more than 140 million people monthly worldwide through its trusted journalism, signature ForbesLive events and 49 licensed local editions in 81 countries.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;We are seeking a Director, Enterprise AI Operations to lead the design and execution of AI operations across Forbes.&lt;br&gt;This is an internal-facing role focused on transforming how teams operate, not building external AI products. This is not a traditional product role, and it is not an AI experimentation role. We are not looking to explore AI. We are looking to operationalize it across the company.&lt;br&gt;This role is for a leader who has successfully driven operational transformation at scale and knows how to move organizations from ideas to adoption, and from tools to sustained behavioral change. Working closely with executive leadership, this person will help execute Forbes’s enterprise AI enablement &amp;amp; operational strategy by embedding AI into the core workflows that power Editorial, Audience, Revenue, and internal operations.&lt;br&gt;You will be responsible for operationalizing a focused set of high-impact initiatives that integrate AI into day-to-day workflows and drive measurable business outcomes. Success in this role is not defined by experimentation or feature delivery, but by adoption, operational efficiency, improved decision-making, and measurable organizational impact.&lt;br&gt;This role will partner cross-functionally across Product, Technology, Editorial, Revenue, Audience, Legal, HR, and Operations to ensure AI becomes a sustainable operating layer across the business. This is a high-impact leadership role focused on execution, enablement, governance, and organizational transformation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;br&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;AI Operations &amp;amp; Execution&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Execute and operationalize Forbes’s internal AI roadmap in partnership with executive leadership.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive implementation of a focused set of high-impact AI initiatives that materially improve workflows and business outcomes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Translate strategic priorities into scalable operational programs, processes, and execution plans.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure AI capabilities are embedded into existing workflows and systems rather than operating as parallel or optional tools.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner closely with Product and Engineering teams to support the successful deployment and integration of AI capabilities across the organization.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cross-Functional Enablement &amp;amp; Change Management&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead enterprise-wide AI adoption efforts across Editorial, Audience Development, Consumer Revenue, Advertising, and corporate functions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and scale repeatable enablement systems, training programs, and operational playbooks that drive sustained behavioral change.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own change management processes end-to-end, proactively identifying resistance points, gathering feedback, and partnering with department leaders to improve adoption.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and manage an internal AI community of practice to share knowledge, best practices, and workflow innovations across teams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with HR and organizational leadership to support workforce readiness and AI literacy initiatives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
