&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Forbes is an iconic global media brand that has symbolized success for over a century. Fueled by journalism that informs and inspires, Forbes spotlights the doers and doings shaping industries, achieving success and making an impact on the world. Forbes connects and convenes the most influential communities ranging from billionaires, business leaders and rising entrepreneurs to creators and innovators. The Forbes brand reaches more than 140 million people monthly worldwide through its trusted journalism, signature ForbesLive events and 49 licensed local editions in 81 countries.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;The 2024 ADWEEK Experiential Awards Winner: Experiential Brand of the Year, ForbesLive produces premium conferences and experiences that connect influential leaders, entrepreneurs, and visionaries. Our events combine thought leadership, networking opportunities, and exclusive content to create memorable experiences.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Forbes seeks a strategic, highly motivated events professional to join our ForbesLive team as Director of Logistics, reporting directly to the Executive Director, ForbesLive. This individual brings deep expertise in event logistics and operations, a strong command of vendor and budget management, and the leadership presence to drive flawless execution across a dynamic portfolio of live events produced virtually, in person, and in hybrid formats—both domestically and internationally. The Director of Logistics will serve as a key operational leader on the ForbesLive team, ensuring every event is executed at the highest standard while building scalable systems and processes that support the team&#39;s continued growth.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role operates in a fast-paced, live event environment where adaptability, responsiveness, and a team-first mindset are critical to success.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;:&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Logistics &amp;amp; Operations Leadership&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&amp;nbsp; Lead end-to-end logistics planning and execution across ForbesLive&#39;s portfolio of events, ensuring seamless operational delivery from pre-event planning through on-site execution and post-event wrap&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&amp;nbsp; Establish and maintain scalable logistics systems, processes, and best practices that support a growing event portfolio&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&amp;nbsp; Serve as the primary operational point of contact on-site at assigned events, overseeing and managing external and internal event staff, vendors, and day-of logistics&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&amp;nbsp; Build and maintain relevant event documents not limited to event timelines, security plans, floor plans, and run-of-show documents; ensure all logistics documentation is current and accessible across the team&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Vendor &amp;amp; Budget Management&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&amp;nbsp; Lead vendor strategy and selection across all event categories (venues, catering, florals, A/V, staffing, transportation); negotiate partner contracts (in partnership with legal)&amp;nbsp; and manage vendor relationships throughout the event lifecycle&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&amp;nbsp; Own and maintain a comprehensive vendor database including contacts, capacity, budget benchmarks, and availability&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&amp;nbsp; Manage overall logistics budgets and expense tracking; submit and route invoices for approval; ensure budgets are reconciled accurately and on time&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Cross-Functional Partnership&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&amp;nbsp; Establish position as a key leader on the ForbesLive team; liaise with internal stakeholders working across the events to ensure operational alignment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&amp;nbsp; Lead cross-departmental planning meetings for assigned events; tracking next steps

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Forbes is an iconic global media brand that has symbolized success for over a century. Fueled by journalism that informs and inspires, Forbes spotlights the doers and doings shaping industries, achieving success and making an impact on the world. Forbes connects and convenes the most influential communities ranging from billionaires, business leaders and rising entrepreneurs to creators and innovators. The Forbes brand reaches more than 140 million people monthly worldwide through its trusted journalism, signature ForbesLive events and 49 licensed local editions in 81 countries.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Forbes is recruiting for Journalists to join our Editorial Fellowship, a twelve-month immersive training program for early career business journalists who will rotate through our newsroom in order to learn targeted skills specific to a Forbes career. We are looking for recent college graduates who embody the Forbes entrepreneurial spirit to innovate and who are passionate about learning.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;We strongly encourage people from historically underrepresented communities to apply.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the role:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Fellowship will begin with a week-long business journalism bootcamp, a series of classes taught by top editors. Fellows will then rotate through the newsroom during a series of four, 3-month assignments in order to develop financial analysis, investigations, source development, and news reporting.&amp;nbsp;We are looking for recent college graduates who are interested in business journalism and have some experience in reporting, including internships and work on college newspapers. People making a career switch to journalism will also be considered, depending on their previous experience, training and education.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Our office operates as a remote and hybrid workforce, with in-person collaboration expected for certain roles. Based on the responsibilities of this position, a hybrid work schedule with a minimum of one in-person collaboration day per week at our Jersey City, NJ headquarters is expected.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop the skills related to pitching, reporting and writing breaking news, trend pieces, second day takes, and feature length business stories.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work on wealth valuations and financial investigations focused on the world’s wealthiest people.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work alongside veteran reporters to cultivate sources and find scoops.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct research related to list rankings (contact sources, gather documents and data, write short profiles).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Fact-check the Daily Cover Story on Forbes.com and magazine stories.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with Forbes staffers on special projects.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The ideal candidate:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Recent college graduates from either undergraduate or graduate programs. Candidates must have graduated within the past 24 months.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Journalism major, significant roles at a collegiate publication, OR previous journalism internship is required.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prior experience in fact-checking, reporting, writing, and editing.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Solid news judgment with an understanding of journalistic standards and editorial ethics.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with publishing platforms, current digital and social media technologies and SEO best practices.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong interest in business/entrepreneurship and understanding of basic financial terms/figures.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to understand and draw conclusions from financial documents.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong written and oral communication skills.&lt;/li&gt

